Release v1.5.0

New external dependency (KirigamiAddons), KConfig XT migration, icon store refactor, batch-selection removal, significant UI rework.

Changelog since v1.4.0:

Bug fix: pendingLoads stuck at non-zero — synchronous cache hits in refresh() decremented before m_pendingLoads was assigned; assignment now precedes all loadMetadataForRow dispatches
Bug fix: dataChanged in applyMetadata and toggleDesktopLink now passes role hints (was empty, causing full-row re-evaluation on every metadata load)
Removed: Batch selection mode (selectionMode, IsSelectedRole, setSelected, selectAll, clearSelection, selectedPaths, trashSelected) — fully removed from model
Removed: StorageDialog.qml
New dep: KF6KirigamiAddons — FormCard used in SettingsDialog
New: Theme.qml singleton — cardBorderColor extracted from inline duplication in Dashboard + Settings
New: AppImageIconStore — process-wide icon byte singleton; AppImageIconProvider now only holds per-engine pixmap render cache, m_iconsLock removed from provider
New: KConfig XT schema (appimagemanagersettings.kcfg) — AppSettings delegates to generated AppImageManagerSettings::self() instead of raw KConfigGroup
Perf: findRowByPath O(1) via m_pathIndex hash (was linear scan)
UI: Dashboard delegate replaced custom Item+Rectangle+MouseArea with Controls.ItemDelegate; uniform selection highlight via explicit insets + verticalPadding
UI: Dashboard vertical + horizontal pane separators removed
UI: Dashboard detailScrollView outer vertical scrollbar hidden
UI: ManageWindow drag icon — separate floating dragIcon surrogate, original fades to 30% opacity during drag
UI: SettingsDialog uses FormCard, dialog size 24×28 → 28×34 gridUnits
